{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_45","type":"agent_message","text":"I fixed the failure behind the provided reproducer command, which targets `org.apache.kafka:kafka-clients:3.5.2` rather than `org.apache.hadoop:hadoop-mapreduce-client-app:2.7.3`. The issue was a hard-coded embedded Kafka listener on `localhost:9092`, so the native test failed whenever that port was already in use. I changed [KafkaClientsTest.java](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge9/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2969-b4447c57/tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/3.5.1/src/test/java/org_apache_kafka/kafka_clients/KafkaClientsTest.java:84) to allocate a free local port at startup and reuse that address for the broker, admin client, producer, and consumer.\n\nVerification passed with:\n```bash\nGRAALVM_HOME=/home/vjovanov/gdrive/bin/graalvm-jdk-25.0.3+9.1 \\\nGVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=current-defaults \\\nJAVA_HOME=/home/vjovanov/gdrive/bin/graalvm-jdk-25.0.3+9.1 \\\n./gradlew testInfra -Pcoordinates=org.apache.kafka:kafka-clients:3.5.2 -Pparallelism=1 --stacktrace\n```\n\nResult: `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` and `All commands succeeded for coordinates=org.apache.kafka:kafka-clients:3.5.2.`\n\nThe worktree also contains unrelated pre-existing modified `stats/.../stats.json` files; I left those untouched."}}
